ian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Attendees-2-320x169.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Attendees-2-640x338.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Attendees-2-600x316.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /> Meditol is a medicated and antiseptic soap range has 6 variants, each with unique ingredients that prevent and cure common skin problems. Its Antibacterial and Anti-mosquito range is a combination of bacteria-fighting ingredients with mosquito repellent fragrances. The line was introduced to the portfolio to help reduce the rate of malaria in Nigeria by keeping mosquitoes at bay. World Malaria Day is a global event tied in recognizing efforts to end malaria hence it will serve as an opportunity to introduce the brand around that time, thereby creating awareness and communicating our solution to fighting the disease. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-926632 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195.jpg" alt="" width="940" height="951" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195.jpg 750w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195-591x598.jpg 591w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195-487x493.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195-237x240.jpg 237w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195-474x480.jpg 474w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/IMG_9195-593x600.jpg 593w" sizes="(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px" />Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/Meditol-NG Instagram: @Meditolnigeria